[normal]Foreign Office 
[normal](
[normal]&amp; then the 
[normal]FCO
[normal])
[normal] from 1948 to 1973, and was
[normal],
[normal] from 1968 to 1970
[normal],
[normal] Head of the 
[normal]Science &amp; Technology 
[normal]Department
[normal],
[normal] which handled FCO interests in all 
[normal]q
[normal]uestions
[normal] conc
[normal]erning the environment, the sea
[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]bed and the peaceful uses of atomic energy
[normal]. I served in 
[normal]senior positions 
[normal]as an Official of 
[normal]the European Commission from 1973 to 1986
[normal];
[normal] and was for the last 5 of these years 
[normal]- which included the period of the 
[normal]Chernobyl
[normal] disaster - 
[normal]Head of the Directorate General for Energy
[normal], which handled all 
[normal]energy issues
[normal].
[normal] Since retirement
[normal],
[normal] my relevant experience has been to serve 
[normal]as a founder Patron of "Supporters of Nuclear Energy (SONE)"; 
[normal]as 
[normal]Vice-President an
[normal]d
[normal] later as 
[normal]Executive President of Europa Nostra
[normal] - the leading European level Heritage NGO
[normal];
[normal] and also as founder Chairman of Friends of Eden, Lakeland &amp; Lunesdale Scenery
